{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> μοχλός</b> <br /> (<i>Ionic dialect</i> μοκλός [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.BC: Anacreon Lyricus 88)\">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>], ὁ, <b>bar, lever, crowbar</b>, used for moving ships, μοχλοῖσιν δ᾽ ἄρα τήν γε κατείρυσεν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 5.261 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; or heavy weights, μοχλοῖς καὶ μηχαναῖσιν ἀνελκύσαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Pax” 307 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; for forcing doors and gates, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Orestes” 1474 (Lyric poetry), compare “Ba.” 348, 1104, etc.; ὑποβαλόντες τοὺς μ. ὑπὸ τὰς πύλας 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Lysistrata” 428, compare 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Mechanica” 847b11, +others \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>any bar</b> or <b>stake</b>, as in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 9.332 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] the stake which Odysseus runs into the Cyclops' eye,[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"compare 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Cyclops” 633. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> wooden or iron <b>bar</b> or <b>bolt</b> placed across gates on the inside and secured by the βάλανος, τοῦ μοχλοῦ διακοπέντος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 4.111, compare 2.4, “IG” 12.313.126; μοχλοὺς ἐπιβάλλειν 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Thesmophoriazusae” 415; τὸν μ. ἐμβάλλειν 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 7.1.12, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Lysistrata” 246; μοχλοῖς καὶ κλῄθροισι τὰ προπύλαια πακτοῦν [prev. work] 264; τὴν πόλιν.. ἀπεκλῄσατε τοῖσι μ. [prev. work] 487 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; πύλας μοχλοῖς χαλᾶτε by [drawing back] <b>the bars</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Choephori” 879; κλῇθρα λύσαντες μοχλοῖς 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Iphigenia Taurica” 99 (more naturally κλῄθρων μοχλοὺς λύσαντες, as in 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Lysistrata” 310 κἂν μὴ.. τοὺς μοχλοὺς χαλῶσιν): _metaphorically_, μέγας σοι τοῦδ᾽ ἐγὼ φόβου μ.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] <b>a bar</b> or <b>defence against</b> fear. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 760. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G8352","accentedUnicode":"μοχλός","shortDef":"a bar","mediumDef":"a bar","stepGloss":"a bar","stepTransliteration":"mochlos","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}